rComments: Very sweet and caring prof. Her lectures are easy to follow and the readings are really interesting. Strongly encourages participation and she's always available for questions outside of class hours. Very clear expectations and super fair exams.

Real easy class but I think that's just the course and not her. You have to participate in lectures to get marks but never specifies what qualifies as A+ participation. Monotone and boring because content requires you to understand basic differences/struggles between genders. However, she's biased towards woman problems which was problematic.

Dr. Eksi is amazing! Truly a gem. She has clear expectations. Basically just read the assigned material (all provided via online course pdfs, no cost $ :)), and try to discuss. Don't underestimate her disarming presentation. Listen carefully and you will soon understand that she is brilliant. Don't care what anyone else says, she's the G.O.A.T.
She is a pretty decent professor. Her voice might platonic at times, but the course content is interesting.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Participation matters', 'Get ready to read']
